This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically image segmentation, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new network architecture and training strategy, which involves deep learning techniques, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of adaptive weighting and target adaptive loss, which are related to artificial intelligence and optimization, respectively, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also evaluates its proposed method on publicly available datasets, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of deep neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
